headlines.shortLinkText: Leeds fears grow after 4-1 loss at Bournemouth

headlines.description: — Erling Haaland scored his 50th goal of the season as Manchester City moved to the top of the Premier League on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Haaland scores 50th goal of season, Man City goes top of EPL

headlines.description: — There were protests at the start but celebrations at the end as Manchester United edged toward a return to the Champions League on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fernandes fires Man United toward the Champions League

headlines.description: Newcastle United look almost certain to be playing in the Champions League next season after scoring two late to beat Southampton.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wilson double puts Newcastle on brink of Champions League

headlines.description: — Substitute Diogo Jota scored a stoppage-time winner as Liverpool beat Tottenham 4-3 after a wild finish to their Premier League game on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wild finish as Liverpool beats Tottenham 4-3
